SARS - WORLDWIDE (139): CASES
***************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
[Note: as SARS activity has been decreasing, many of the official
websites are not posting updates on the weekends (Saturday and
Sunday). ProMED-mail will continue to monitor official websites and
post material as it becomes available. ProMED-mail will also monitor
newswire reports, but will continue to exercise prudence in posting
from newswires, as many "suspected" cases reported through newswires
are later found to have other etiologies. - Mod. MPP]
In this update:
[1] Hong Kong - DOH
[2] China - Beijing Government
[3] Taiwan - CDC Taiwan
******
[1]
Date: 7 Jun 2003
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Hong Kong Department of Health [edited]
<http://www.info.gov.hk/dh/new/2003/03-06-07e.htm>

Situation report on Severe Acute Respiratory Syndrome 7 Jun 2003
The following is jointly issued by the Department of Health and the
Hospital Authority:
There are 2 newly confirmed cases of Severe Acute Respiratory
Syndrome (SARS) today (7 Jun 2003), the 23rd consecutive day on which
the number of cases has fallen below 5 since 16 May 2003.
The [newly reported] cases involve 2 elderly women who are believed
to have contracted SARS during their stay in hospital. One of
patients was admitted to North District Hospital on 22 May 2003 and
was transferred to Alice Ho Miu Ling Nethersole Hospital on 3 Jun
2003. The other patient was admitted to Caritas Medical Centre on 1
Apr 2003.
10 more patients had recovered from the disease and been discharged
from hospital, [bringing the total number of recovered patients] to
1360.
The number of SARS patients in intensive care units is 20. They are
among the 73 cases under treatment in hospitals. 33 are recovering
patients in convalescence and in preparation for discharge. No
fatality was reported. The cumulative total of deaths relating to
SARS remains at 286.
The cumulative figure for patients who have been admitted to public
hospitals with SARS since 12 Mar 2003 is as follows:
Cumulative no. cases/ total no. discharged patients/ total no. deaths
(change in past 24 hours presented in parentheses with minus for decrease.)
Health care workers of Hospitals/Clinics and medical students: 386
(0)/ 358 (0)/ (n/a)
Patients, family members & visitors: 1366 (2)/ 1002 (10)/ (n/a)
Total: 1752 (2)/ 1360 (10)/ 286 (0)
Total in hospital: 106 (-8)
Recovering patients in convalescence: 33
Cases under treatment: 73 (2) (including 20 patients in intensive care units)
Suspected cases: 7
--
