SARS Bulletin
Daily Report on Number of SARS Cases on the Chinese Mainland (June 7)
MOH, P.R.China 7 Jun 2003
From: 1 Nov 2002 To: June 7, 2003, BJT 10:00
Province: Cumulative no. case(s)/ no. new cases/ no. recovered/ no.
deaths/ no. suspected cases
Beijing: 2523/ 1/ 1446/ 183/ 668
Hebei: 215/ 0/ 191/ 12/ 0
Hubei: 7/ 0/ 6/ 1/ 3
Inner Mongolia: 284/ 0/ 207/ 29/ 32
Liaonin: 7/ 0/ 2/ 2/ 1
Shanghai: 8/ 0/ 3/ 2/ 0
Shanxi: 448/ 0/ 375/ 23/ 4
Sichuan: 20/ 0/ 16/ 2/ 1
Total: 5330/ 1/ 3934/ 338/ 800
Note: the total figure includes the latest numbers of SARS cases in
the other 18 SARS-affected regions, namely, Heilongjiang, Xinjiang,
Gansu, Jiangsu, Anhui, Shaanxi, Zhejiang, Henan, Chongqing, Jiangxi,
Ningxia, Shandong, Fujian, Hunan, Guangdong, Jilin, Tianjin, and
Guangxi. In total, the 17 regions had reported 1818 cumulative
confirmed SARS cases, 101 suspected cases, 1684 discharged patients,
as well as 84 deaths.
[Individual reports on provinces not having reported cases in 20 days
or more are no longer provided. - Mod.MPP]
