[3]
Date: 7 Jun 2003
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: CDC Taiwan [edited]
<http://www.cdc.gov.tw/sarsen/>

No. new probable cases reported: 2
Cumulative no. cases: 677
(cumulative no. cases in last update: 676)
Explanation: 4 probable cases have been cancelled by reporting
physician(s); 3 previously reported [suspected] cases have been
reclassified as probable cases by reporting physician(s)
Cumulative no. SARS probable cases, by geographic area: 6 Jun 2003 9 AM
Area: Cumulative no. cases/ no. new probable cases reported/ no.
discharged/ total no. deaths
North: 518/ 2/ 154/ 56 (3 prob. cases cancelled; 3 susp. cases
reclassified as prob. by reporting MD)
Central: 38/ 0/ 0/ 3
South: 114/ 0/ 61/ 21 (1 prob. case cancelled by reporting MD)
East: 7/ 0/ 0/ 1
Total: 677/ 2/ 215/ 81 (4 prob. cases cancelled; 5 [susp] cases
reclassified as prob. by reporting MDs)
As mentioned in earlier updates, there are graphics at the above
website link. According to the pie chart representation of reported
cases, there are an additional 1394 suspected cases reported, and 723
formerly reported cases (suspected and probable) have been excluded.
Reviewing the epidemic curve on today's update page, the most recent
noted date of onset is 3 Jun 2003.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[In the past 24 hours there have been 2 new probable cases reported
in Hong Kong, 2 new probable cases in Taiwan (with an additional 3
suspected cases reclassified as probable cases), and 1 new probable
case in China (Beijing). There was no official Health Canada or
Ontario Ministry of Health and Long-Term Care update available, and
newswires did not mention additional new cases since yesterday's
report. - Mod.MPP]
